
 TexTron Snake
 ==============================

 TexTron Snake is very simple ascii snake game tributed to Tron legacy.
 It was meant to be developed as a collaborative programming execises
 on Open Source Systems for undergraduate CS students.

 INSTALL
 --------------------------------------------------

 * Quick instructions:

 If you obtained the source from the VCS repository
 
 $ ./autogen.sh
 $ ./configure
 $ make

 Optionally, if you wish to build and install the software under /tmp/foo

 $ ./autogen.sh
 $ ./configure --prefix=/tmp/foo
 $ make
 $ make install

 Scene files are installed under $(prefix)/share/textronsnake.

 You'll need libncurses and pthread support to build the software.

 * Detailed instructions: read INSTALL

 PROGRAM EXECUTION
 --------------------------------------------------

 Usage:  textronsnake 


 FUNCTIONALITY
 --------------------------------------------------

 The program will load scene files from the scenes directory.

 Controls:

	+   decrease the game speed
	-   increase the game speed 
	q   quit the game (also skip intro)


